SIMPLE: if
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: If
<hw>If</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>conj.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>if</ets>,
<ets>gif</ets>, AS. <ets>gif</ets>; akin to OFries. <ets>ief</ets>,
<ets>gef</ets>, <ets>ef</ets>, OS. <ets>ef</ets>, <ets>of</ets>, D.
<ets>of</ets>, or, whether, if, G. <ets>ob</ets> whether, if, OHG.
<ets>oba</ets>, <ets>ibu</ets>, Icel. <ets>ef</ets>, Goth.
<ets>iba</ets>, <ets>ibai</ets>, an interrogative particle; properly a
case form of a noun meaning, doubt (cf. OHG. <ets>iba</ets> doubt,
condition, Icel. <ets>if</ets>, <ets>ef</ets>, <ets>ifi</ets>,
<ets>efi</ets>), and therefore orig. meaning, on condition that.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>In case that; granting, allowing, or supposing that; --
introducing a condition or supposition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Tisiphone, that oft hast heard my prayer,⟦br⟧
Assist, <qex>if</qex> ⟦OE⟧dipus deserve thy care.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>If</qex> thou be the Son of God, command that these stones be
made bread.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. iv. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Whether; -- in dependent questions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Uncertain <qex>if</qex> by augury or chance.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She doubts <qex>if</qex> two and two make four.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>As if</b></col>, <col><b>But if</b></col></mcol>.
<cd>See under <er>As</er>, <er>But</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>I' faith</ent>⟦br⟧
